title: Review: Consistency is key at Kolache Kitchen
text: Review: Consistency is key at Kolache Kitchen Review: Consistency is key at Kolache Kitchen Advocate staff photo by Kyle Peveto -- A ranchero, a sweet bread filled with eggs and bacon or sausage is a hearty breakfast option at the Kolache Kitchen on Jefferson Highway. Advocate staff photo by Kyle Peveto -- The Cuban sandwich is one of the lunch items from the Kolache Kitchen on Jefferson Highway. Advocate staff photo by Kyle Peveto -- The Kolache Kitchen on Jefferson Highway sells savory Texas-style kolaches made with sweet bread and sausage. The boudin variety has a Louisiana touch. Advocate staff photo by Kyle Peveto -- Sweet fruit kolaches, an American take on a Czech bakery, are made daily at the Kolache Kitchen on Jefferson Highway. Kyle Peveto | kpeveto@theadvocate.com
